      "data": {
        "title": "Where This Applies",
        "body": "Use this contract when stamping instances from bridges, creating templated planning nodes, cloning graphs, migrating old nodes, loading a node from disk as `root.node` plus connected fragments, checking whether connected files declare fragment status by carrying a type node of type `fragment`, projecting sibling `.node` files through a runtime-generated root, determining whether that node is single-file or multi-file, or validating whether a node instance is complete enough to render through its class views.",
        "conditions": [
          "A class-backed node is created from a bridge or template.",
          "A graph file contains a node with a custom or class-backed type.",
          "Renderer code needs to resolve node.web or editor.web from bound class metadata.",
          "A planning/task graph clones nodes that should remain real instances.",
          "Binding integrity, legal fragment adjacency, or root-only port exposure must be enforced."
